•Divide and Conquer

#Uses :- 
•credit scoring models
•study of customer behaviour
•diagnosis of medical conditions

#Cons :- 
•data with large number of nominal features or large number of numeric features, may result in overly complex trees
•tendency of overfitting

#Methods for splitting Criteria
•Gini Impurity
•Entropy
•Information Gain
•Variance Reduction (Regression)

#Types:- 
•Classification trees :-  used for categorical outcomes
•Regression tress :- used for continuous outcomes


